The paper proposes a reactive navigation framework for mobile robots, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The approach employs heuristic evaluations and sampling on tentacles, which involves artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The framework also deals with obstacle avoidance and path planning, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents statistical results from simulations, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG) for performance evaluation.
